            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#AA">
                <p>Sacred to Mercury Augustus, when Orfitus and Pudens were consuls, [and] Alfius Plocamus was tax-collector, and A[---]?. The master [of the college?] was Antonius Severus.
                   [Column a] Virius Eutyches, Appaeus Primigenius, Statius Valerius, Herbonius Atquisitus, Ocusius Thallus, Speratio slave of Toticus, Cosmio slave of Synetus, Pompeius Telesphorinus, 
                   Myrinus slave of Agrippina, Usonius Dionysius, [and] Restius Aper, [---].    
                   [Column b] Virius Synhetus, Messor slave of Lollia, Minicius Vitalis, Euhelpistus slave of Novus, Regontius Antoninus, Mamilius Semnus, Artiscius Hermes, Peticius Severus,
                   Myrinus slave of the Titii, Cornelius Secundius, Vettidius Dionysius, Valerius [---]?
                </p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>In line 3, the "F" of "Alfio" appears to have been rendered as an "E".</p> 
            </div>
